T1  - Less Volume, More Variety: An Inverse Relationship Between LLM Output Length and Contrarian Discovery in Pharmaceutical Stock Selection
AU  - Kim, HoKwang
A1  - Dennis Kim
PY  - 2026
DA  - 2026/05/11
PB  - SSRN
M3  - SSRN Working Paper
SN  - 6705598
DO  - 10.2139/ssrn.6705598
UR  - https://ssrn.com/abstract=6705598
AB  - Under identical prompts to four frontier LLMs (ChatGPT, Claude, DeepSeek, Gemini), shorter-output models produce proportionally more contrarian stock picks. Spearman rank correlation between output length and contrarian discovery rate is -0.80 across four models and -1.00 excluding a stale-data outlier. Proposes a compression-forces-selection mechanism and outlines a five-study research agenda.
