T1  - Directional Decoupling: Volatility-Ratio-Driven Beta Compression in the BNB-ETH Pair, May 2022 – April 2026
AU  - Kim, HoKwang
A1  - Dennis Kim
PY  - 2026
DA  - 2026/05/12
PB  - SSRN
M3  - SSRN Working Paper
SN  - 6750298
DO  - 10.2139/ssrn.6750298
UR  - https://ssrn.com/abstract=6750298
AB  - Documents an instance of channel-specific beta change in BNB-ETH, May 2022 to April 2026. Static beta falls 16.9 percent while the Pearson correlation is essentially unchanged. A formal variance decomposition attributes 100 percent of the beta change to the volatility-ratio channel. DCC-GARCH dynamic-conditional-beta confirms the direction. Formalizes 'directional decoupling' as a distinct phenomenon from co-movement weakening.
